problem link : https://leetcode.com/problems/contiguous-array/description/

Intuition
In this problem we need to find subarray of max length which has equal ones and zeros , so we can understand that the count of zeros - count of ones in that subarray will be equal to 0 , suppose we have a current prefix at index i with diff of zero_count and one_count as diff , suppose we find a previous prefix with same diff as the current prefix , then remaining subarray will have diff = 0, as If a previous prefix has the same diff, then subtracting the two prefix differences gives 0, hence we use a hash map to store the first occurences of indices of diff , as the first occurence will have the highest chance of creating a max subarray .

Approach
we initalize zero_counter , one_counter and result to 0 as initally subarray is empty , we also create a hash map to store firct occurence of diff,

traverse the array
at index check the zero_count and one_count and update them , calculate the difference in zero and one count,

if diff = 0 , we have find a correct subarray find it length and store it in result store it in result

if diff is not seen before in hashmap:
store firct occurence of diff index i in hash map

else when diff already in hash map there will be subarray of length i - f[diff] which will have equal count of zero and one , update result

return result as max length of subarray with equal ones and zeros

Complexity
Time complexity:
O(n)

Space complexity:
O(n)

Code
class Solution:
    def findMaxLength(self, nums: List[int]) -> int:
        zero_counter = one_counter = result = 0
        f = {}

        for i in range(len(nums)):
            if nums[i] == 0:
                zero_counter += 1
            else:
                one_counter += 1
            diff = (zero_counter - one_counter)
            if diff == 0:
                result = max(result , i +1)
            if diff not in f:
                f[diff] = i
            else:
                result = max(result,i - f[diff])
        return result
